'''耳廓'''（英文：Auricle 或 auricula 或 pinna）是[[外耳|外耳]]在体外可见的部分，可收集[[声波|声波]]<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Video: 外耳解剖|url=https://www.msdmanuals.cn/home/multimedia/video/v43437678_zh|accessdate=2021-03-07|work=《默克诊疗手册家庭版》|language=zh-CN}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=External ear {{!}} Radiology Reference Article {{!}} Radiopaedia.org|url=https://radiopaedia.org/articles/external-ear?lang=us|accessdate=2021-03-07|last=Gaillard|first=Frank|work=Radiopaedia|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-04-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210429095937/https://radiopaedia.org/articles/external-ear?lang=us|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 结构 ==
耳廓的核心支撑为[[弹性软骨|弹性软骨]]，在[[解剖学|解剖学]]上包括{{link-en|耳轮|Helix (ear)}}、{{link-en|对耳轮|Antihelix}}、[[耳垂|耳垂]]、[[耳屏|耳屏]]等结构<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite web|title=人体解剖学/外耳|url=http://www.a-hospital.com/w/%E4%BA%BA%E4%BD%93%E8%A7%A3%E5%89%96%E5%AD%A6/%E5%A4%96%E8%80%B3|accessdate=2021-03-07|work=|publisher=www.a-hospital.com|archive-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200208220331/http://www.a-hospital.com/w/%E4%BA%BA%E4%BD%93%E8%A7%A3%E5%89%96%E5%AD%A6/%E5%A4%96%E8%80%B3|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 功能 ==
人耳廓与[[外耳道|外耳道]]一同构成[[外耳|外耳]]，并通过外耳道传至[[中耳|中耳]][[鼓膜|鼓膜]]处。除了收集声波外，耳廓、鼓膜对声音有一定放大作用，对于1500-7000[[赫兹|赫兹]]的声音，[[声强|声强]]可以提高10-15[[分贝|分贝]]<ref>{{Cite book|chapter=|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3jvUDAAAQBAJ&pg=PT237&lpg=PT237&dq=Auricle+amplification+1.5-7khz&source=bl&ots=-Y-RWs1cOF&sig=ACfU3U0F_TwejWbNuCqXKeLzQr4t-rKX3A&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjG46ztpp3vAhUwmuAKHR7BCCkQ6AEwEXoECBYQAw#v=onepage&q=Auricle%20amplification%201.5-7khz&f=false|publisher=Psychology Press|date=2016-08-12|isbn=978-1-317-37254-7|language=en|first=George|last=Mather|title=Foundations of Sensation and Perception}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=How the Ear Works|url=https://www.hopkinsmedicine.org/health/conditions-and-diseases/how-the-ear-works|accessdate=2021-03-07|work=www.hopkinsmedicine.org|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210123054018/https://www.hopkinsmedicine.org/health/conditions-and-diseases/how-the-ear-works|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

